race.comment: ICEWATER (2) is still in his first prep and coming along nicely. Wound up from midfield on the bend to record an impressive maiden win last start over 1590m at Ballina. Needs a solid tempo which is the query, but he continues to improve and is good enough to win at this level. Lightly raced filly PRESTIGE ICE (6) races beyond 1250m for the first time. Lacked a turn of foot when she missed the placings last time out at Ballina. Should race up on the speed and without too much pressure likely she will give backers a great sight. TARA KODA (5) is her own worst enemy, bungling the start at all three outings this prep. Hasn't been beaten far in each of those runs and now gets out over a bit more ground. Should be strong late. REEL TORQUE (3) ran a better race at Grafton last time and is worth including at decent odds.
